(127, 'Wrist extension', 'Sit in a chair. Hold a hand weight in your right hand. Lean your forearm on your thigh or a table. Keep your forearm in place and bend your wrist upward. Slowly lower the hand weight back ', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Stroke', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65a8e07a60646_Mwristrotation.jpg', 'This stroke hand exercise is like a bicep curl, but for your wrist, and is helpful for improving grip function. Hold the water bottle in your affected hand and use your non-affected hand to support your arm. Allow your wrist to stretch down, and then curl your wrist up.', NULL),
(128, 'Core rotation', 'Raise your legs so that they\'re perpendicular to the floor. This is the starting position. Keeping your head and shoulders on the floor, raise your hips and twist them to the right, so that your legs rotate in the same direction. Return to the starting position, and repeat, \r\n this time twisting your hips to your left.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Stroke', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65a8e11da23c6_Mcorerotation.jpeg', 'Rehabilitation training of core muscle stability can effectively improve the balance function and walking speed of stroke patients, probably by increasing the thickness of transverse abdominis muscle.', NULL),
(130, 'Hand tretches', 'old one hand at chest level with the elbow bent. With the other hand, grasp the thumb side of the hand and bend your wrist downward. \r\nTo increase the stretch, bend your wrist toward your little finger. Repeat the same exercise with a straight arm. Switch hands and repeat.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65af666e01a2c_Mhandstretches.jpg', 'Strengthen the muscles around the joints for better support. Increase the circulation of synovial fluid (lubricates and helps cushion the joints to keep them moving smoothly). Improve blood flow to your hands, warming the muscles and ligaments.\r\n', NULL),
(131, 'Grip Stretch', 'Fingers back, palms on the desk: Stretch by leaning back and forth on your bodyweight and gently side to side.Fingers back, palms off the desk: Lifting your palms up places the emphasis on your fingers more.Clenched fists: While seated, place your hands on your things with palms up.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65af66c18c48d_Mgripstretch.jpg', 'Reduced hand aging process. Increased muscle and skeletal mass .Increased independence to engage in everyday tasks. Improved cognitive, physical and overall holistic health.', NULL),
(132, 'Tendon Glides', 'Bend both the knuckle and middle finger joints so that your fingers are resting on the base of your palm. Keep your fingers straight. From the open-palm position, slowly engage all your fingers, thumb, and joints to create a fist and squeeze gently.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65af67102a18d_Mtendonglides.png', 'Tendon glide exercises can help prevent repetitive trauma to the hands, writs and elbows. There may be some discomfort when starting the exercises,but that should decrease in a day or two. If it does not improve or go away, seek advice from your health care professional.', NULL),
(133, 'Finger Stretch', 'Finger extensor stretch Lay your hand out flat on a table or solid surface. Use your other hand to hold the affected finger.Slowly lift up the finger and keep the rest of your fingers flat. Lift and stretch the finger as high as it will go without straining. Hold it here for a few seconds and release it back down.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65af67edd42fd_mfingerstreching.jpeg', 'The practice of this exercise promotes blood circulation, help release stiffness, and reduces the frequency of cramps, when done as part of both warm-up and cool down.', NULL),
(134, 'hand squeezes', 'Hold a soft ball in your palm and squeeze it as hard as you can.Hold for a few seconds and release.Repeat 10 to 15 times on each hand. Do this exercise two to three times a week, but rest your hands for 48 hours in between sessions.\r\n', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65af6835eef21_Mhandsqueezes.jpg', 'Builds endurance. Increases the power to lift heavy objects. Quality of life. Sports performance is upper .Growth of forearms. Boosts mental health.', NULL),
(135, 'Finger Raising', 'Put your finger on some surface and gently raise one finger one by one at a time.\r\n', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65af686f25176_Mfingerraising.jpg', 'Put your finger on some surface and gently raise one finger one by one at a time.\r\n', NULL),
(136, 'Thumb Touching', 'Start touching your thumb with remaining fingers of hand one by one at a time.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65af68a719287_Mthumbtouching.jpeg', 'This exercise will increase blood circulation in hands and fingers so that it will improve condition of balance and hurting.', NULL),
(137, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65af68e697f9a_Mcalfstretch.jpg', 'Tight calf muscles or injuries can lead to foot and leg pain, including plantar fasciitis, shin splints, Achilles tendonitis, and knee pain. Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility.', NULL),
(138, 'Triceps Stretch', 'Bring your left elbow straight up while bending your arm. Grab your left elbow with your right hand, and pull your left elbow toward  your head with light pressure. If you are more flexible, you may pull your arm slightly behind your head. You will feel the stretch along the back of your arm.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65af692477011_Mtricepstretch.jpg', ' Triceps stretches improve flexibility, lengthen muscles, and increase range of motion. Plus, they can help to prevent tight muscles,loosen connective tissue, and boost circulation, all while using no or minimal equipment.', NULL),
(139, 'Hand stretches', 'Old one hand at chest level with the elbow bent. With the other hand, grasp the thumb side of the hand and bend your wrist downward. To increase the stretch, bend your wrist toward your little finger. Repeat the same exercise with a straight arm. Switch hands and repeat.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65af6961ca757_Mhandstretches.jpg', 'Hand and wrist exercises can improve mobility and decrease the chance of injury or reinjury. Various hand and wrist stretches can help with strengthening. Wrist stretches are easy to do at home or at the office. When done properly, they can benefit a person\'s overall wrist and hand health.', NULL),
(140, 'Tendon Glides', 'Bend both the knuckle and middle finger joints so that your fingers are resting on the base of your palm. Keep your fingers straight. From the open-palm position, slowly engage all your fingers, thumb, and joints to create a fist and squeeze gently.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65af69a99612f_Mtendonglides.png', 'Tendon glide exercises can help prevent repetitive trauma to the hands, writs and elbows. There may be some discomfort when starting the exercises, but that should decrease in a day or two. If it does not improve or go away, seek advice from your health care professional.', NULL),
(141, 'Hand Squeezes', 'Hold a soft ball in your palm and squeeze it as hard as you can. Hold for a few seconds and release.Repeat 10 to 15 times on each hand. Do this exercise two to three times a week, but rest your hands for 48 hours in between sessions.\r\n', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65af6a0b71c54_Mhandsqueezes.jpg', 'Builds endurance. Increases the power to lift heavy objects. Quality of life. Sports performance is upper .Growth of forearms.Boosts mental health.', NULL),
(142, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.\r\n', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65af6a4dc9e6b_Mcalfstretch.jpg', 'Tight calf muscles or injuries can lead to foot and leg pain, including plantar fasciitis, shin splints, Achilles tendonitis, and knee pain. Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility.', NULL),
(143, 'Writting', 'Writting is the best therapy for contraction of muscles of hands.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65af6a874d3dc_Mwriting.jpg', 'The rate of your body will increases which helps to burn calories. Moreover, it also helps in improving the oxygen level and blood flow of the body. When you exercise daily, your brain cells will release frequently. This helps in producing cells in the hippocampus.', NULL),
(146, 'Sit Stand', 'Sit in a chair with your feet apart while holding your hands together in front of your chest. \r\n Without using your hands, push through your feet to stand and hold this position.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c0ec71b08_Msitstand.jpg', 'Improved ability to do everyday activities, such as sitting down, standing up, or climbing stairs without pain. Better balance .Increased mobility, especially in the knees, hips, and ankles.', NULL),
(152, 'Touch Toes', ' Lay on your back, with your legs extending up vertically towards the ceiling. Extend your arms forward, keeping them straight. They should be parallel to your legs. Crunch forwards, reaching up to your toes with your outstretched arms.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c2f72f572_Mtouchtoes.jpg', 'The overall benefit of being able to touch your toes is having proper flexibility in your hamstrings, calves, and lower back. Being able to touch your toes reflects good flexibility in these areas.', NULL),
(154, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c384acbe6_Mcalfstretch.jpg', 'Tight calf muscles or injuries can lead to foot and leg pain, including plantar fasciitis, shin splints, Achilles tendonitis, and knee pain. Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility.', NULL),
(155, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b9b62e8e512_Mwalking.jpeg', 'Much like outdoor walking, walking indoors — either up and down the hallway or in-place — can be beneficial for weight loss if you reach high intensities. A key to maximizing the benefits of at-home walking workouts is by minimizing the sedentary (TV viewing) times and making the most of incidental activities.', NULL),
(156, 'Hip raise', 'Lie on an exercise mat with your knees bent so that your feet are flat on the floor. Keep your back straight.\r\n Place your hands out to your sides palms flat for stability. Raise your glutes off the floor by extending your hips upward while pushing down through you heels.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c3f44eeb9_Mhipraise.jpg', 'Hip raise build strength and size in your glutes in a way many other exercises cannot, and experts agree that they provide benefits for many people, from athletes to older adults over. Glute strength is important for the stabilization of your core, pelvis and lower body.', NULL),
(157, 'Head Side', 'Rotate head gently and slowly from side to side. Do not turn head completely to either side, keep motion small. Keep chin level with ground without letting chin drop to chest.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c43d6ef0a_Mheadside.jpg', 'Improves signals from the brain to body. Improves breathing. Improves posture. Improves balance and coordination. Helps prevent injuries. Helps reduce neck and back pain. Helps release tension and stiffness.', NULL),
(158, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b9b62e8e512_Mwalking.jpeg', 'Much like outdoor walking, walking indoors — either up and down the hallway or in-place — can be beneficial for weight loss if you reach high intensities. A key to maximizing the benefits of at-home walking workouts is by minimizing the sedentary (TV viewing) times and making the most of incidental activities.', NULL),
(159, 'Meditation', 'Meditation is a mind and body practice focused on interactions between the brain, mind, body, and behavior, containing four key elements:a quiet location with little distractions, a comfortable posture, a focus of attention, and an open attitude.\r\n', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c4f03f6b0_Mmeditation.jpg', 'Meditating before a workout will help you relax and de-stress before you get started. It can also help you focus and better control your movements throughout. However, meditating after a workout can reduce your stress hormone levels, reduce pain, and improve your recovery.', NULL),
(160, 'Cat-cow Stretch', 'Keep your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees directly below your hips. Inhale deeply while curving your lower back and bringing your head up, tilting your pelvis up like a \"cow.\" Exhale deeply and bring your abdomen in, arching your spine and bringing your head and pelvis down like a \"cat.\"', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c51a77c32_Mcatstretch.jpeg', 'The stretch allows the body to relieve stress or pain to the lower back and sciatica. Improves flexibility. Cat cow pose increases the flexibility of the neck, shoulders and spine. The movement also stretches the muscles of the hips, back, abdomen and chest.', NULL),
(161, 'Touch Toes', 'Lay on your back, with your legs extending up vertically towards the ceiling. Extend your arms forward, keeping them straight. They should be parallel to your legs. Crunch forwards, reaching up to your toes with your outstretched arms.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c54bdd644_Mtouchtoes.jpg', 'Benefits - The overall benefit of being able to touch your toes is having proper flexibility in your hamstrings, calves, and lower back. Being able to touch your toes reflects good flexibility in these areas.', NULL),
(162, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c621b4517_Mcalfstretch.jpg', 'Tight calf muscles or injuries can lead to foot and leg pain, including plantar fasciitis, shin splints, Achilles tendonitis, and knee pain.\r\n Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility.', NULL),
(163, 'Back Extension', 'Lie on your stomach in a comfortable and spacious area with your hands behind your head. Exhale and raise your chest off the floor by squeezing your gluteus muscles and contracting your lower back. Pause for a second at the top while continuing to squeeze the lower back muscles.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c677315cc_Fbackextension.jpeg', 'Improved back stability. This helps with better posture and better performance during other exercises. Reduced injury risk. Strengthening your back helps you avoid overextending your spine. Improved body awareness. ', NULL),
(164, 'Knee to Chest', 'Start by lying on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor. Next, clasp your hands around one knee and bring that knee up toward your chest.\r\n Hold that knee to your chest, keeping your lower back pressed to the floor.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c6f275f6f_Fkneetochest.jpg', 'Relieve muscle tension in your low back and hips, often related to activities like going up and down the stairs or sitting for long periods of time. Improving flexibility and range of motion in the hips, hamstrings, and glutes.', NULL),
(165, 'Side Plank', 'Lie on your side with your knees bent, and prop your upper body up on your elbow.Raise your hips off the floor, and hold for 6 seconds. Rest for 10 seconds.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c71947c75_Fsideplank.jpg', 'Core strengthening, improve posture,enhance balance, better flexibility , reduce backache , improves metabolism.', NULL),
(166, 'Plank', 'Plant hands directly under shoulders slightly wider than shoulder width\r\n like you\'re about to do a push-up.Ground toes into the floor and squeeze glutes to stabilize your body. Your legs should be working, too — be careful not to lock or hyperextend your knees.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c7500d66a_Fplank.webp', 'Improves posture, improves flexibility , improves metabolism , strengthen core , reduce backache.\r\n', NULL),
(167, 'Cobra Pose', 'Lie down in a prone position. Lie face down on your mat with your entire body extended. Bring your hands underneath the shoulder blades.Begin to lift your upper body Use lower back muscles to lift higher Look slightly forward and up.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c777d8ce6_Fcobra.jpg', 'Opens the shoulder blades, neck, and collar bones.Improves spinal posture, flexibility, and alignment.Reduces back pain.Improves circulation.Opens the lungs.\r\nStimulates the abdominal and digestive organs, improving digestion.Massages and regulates the adrenal and thyroid glands. Reduces stress.', NULL),
(168, 'Bird Dog', 'With your hands under your shoulders and knees under your hips, extend your right leg behind you. At the same time, reach your left arm out in front, parallel to the ground. Hold for two seconds, then repeat on the other side. That\'s one rep.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c7bf3359a_Fbirddog.jpg', 'Improve balance , spinal stability , improve posture, improve range of motion.', NULL),
(169, 'Cat-cow Stretch', 'Keep your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees directly below your hips. Inhale deeply while curving your lower back and bringing your head up, tilting your pelvis up like a \"cow.\" Exhale deeply and bring your abdomen in, arching your spine and bringing your head and pelvis down like a \"cat.\"', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c81be8c38_Fcalfstretch.jpg', 'Stretches muscles,Stimulates abdominal organs, Improves flexibility, Improves posture, Aligns the spine, Back pain relief.', NULL),
(170, 'Side Plank', 'Lie on your side with your knees bent, and prop your upper body up on your elbow. Raise your hips off the floor, and hold for 6 seconds. Rest for 10 seconds.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c87985abf_Fsideplank.jpg', 'Core strengthening, improve posture,enhance balance, better flexibility , reduce backache , improves metabolism.', NULL),
(171, 'Plank', 'Plant hands directly under shoulders (slightly wider than shoulder width) like you\'re about to do a push-up. Ground toes into the floor and squeeze glutes to stabilize your body. Your legs should be working, too — be careful not to lock or hyperextend your knees.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c8ab15bea_Fplank.webp', 'Improves posture , improves flexibility , improves metabolism , strengthen core , reduce backache.', NULL),
(172, 'Seated Forward Fold', 'Sit up on props, bend your knees and use a strap to start with. You want to be able to tilt your pelvis forward and keep length in your spine.\r\n  Engage your thigh muscles and slightly rotate your thighs inwards to spread your sitting bones, giving yourself more room to fold forward.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c94d53b17_Fseatedforward.jpg', 'In this Yogasana, the entire back of the body from head to heels, including the spinal column, is deeply stretched. \r\nThis benefits spine mobility and overall flexibility. It adds to the calmness of the mind and reduces anxiety.', NULL),
(173, 'Thoraic Stretch', 'Sitting tall in a chair with your back resting against the back rest. Take both arms forwards to shoulder height with the hands together. Pause to take a breath in then exhale as you let the arms reach above your head and stretch back over the chair. Pause and return to starting position.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c988dfffb_Fthoraicstretch.jpeg', 'Healthier shoulders. Reduced neck and low back pain. Increased lung volume.', NULL),
(174, 'Side Plank', 'Lie on your side with your knees bent, and prop your upper body up on your elbow. Raise your hips off the floor, and hold for 6 seconds. Rest for 10 seconds.\r\n', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1c9e8de77f_Fsideplank.jpg', 'Core strengthening, improve posture,enhance balance, better flexibility , reduce backache , improves metabolism.', NULL),
(175, 'Plank', 'Plant hands directly under shoulders (slightly wider than shoulder width) like you\'re about to do a push-up. Ground toes into the floor and squeeze glutes to stabilize your body. Your legs should be working, too — be careful not to lock or hyperextend your knees.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1ca822fe9c_Fplank.webp', 'Improves posture , improves flexibility , improves metabolism , strengthen core , reduce backache.', NULL),
(176, 'Donkey Kicks', 'Sitting tall in a chair with your back resting against the back rest. \r\nTake both arms forwards to shoulder height with the hands together. \r\nPause to take a breath in then exhale as you let the arms reach above your head and stretch back over the chair. ', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1caae21c9a_Fdonkeykicks.jpg', 'The donkey kick helps stabilize your core. You have to balance in this position, which strengthens core muscles and gives you better balance in other exercises and daily movements. Starting with donkey kicks can help you activate your glutes more effectively during a workout or run. ', NULL),
(177, 'Eagle Pose', 'You must bend your knees, cross your left thigh over your right, hook the top of your foot behind your right calf, spread the scapula and snug your right elbow into the crook of your left, bring your palms to touch, lift your elbows, and stretch your fingers towards the ceiling.\r\n', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1caded250d_Feagle.jpeg', 'It rings you into present moment focus, providing a deep hip stretch that opens up the back of the lungs and challenges your mind and body awareness.', NULL),
(178, 'Arm Circles', 'Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart or sit in a chair with your back straight and your feet on the floor.Move your arms in a forward circle.\r\nMove your arms in a backward circle.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cb094c7a9_Farmcircle.webp', 'Arm circles can really work on toning the muscles in your shoulder and arm—biceps and triceps. They also work on your upper back muscles. \r\nIf done along with other workouts that target the arm muscles, arm circles can also help reduce the buildup of fat in your arms.\r\n', NULL),
(179, 'Cross Body Arm Stretch', 'Stand up straight, your feet shoulder width apart, \r\nkeep your back straight and hips facing forward, with your arms stretched horizontally to your sides, cross your arms and then bring them out and back as far as you can, stretching your chest, repeat this back and forth motion until the set is complete.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cb3c4d218_Fcrossarmcircle.jpg', 'Relieves tension in the posterior shoulder.Increase mobility.Can help to improve posture. Reduce the risk of injury to the shoulder.Relieves pain in the posterior shoulder.', NULL),
(180, 'Towel Stretch ', 'Whilst in a seated position with your legs out straight, loop a towel around the ball of your foot. Keeping your knee straight, pull the ends of the towel towards you.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cb8de61bb_Ftowelstretch.jpg', 'It helps you deepen stretches if you struggle with flexibility. It can also help you perform many other core exercises. \"A towel can be a really good tool for increasing core strength,\" explained Creveling. \"You can use it for moves like a body saw, knee tucks, and pike-ups.\"', NULL),
(181, 'Wrist Rotation', 'Sit or stand upright. Keeping your forearms by your sides, rotate your hands until your palms are facing up or toward the front of your body.\r\n', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cbe6683ad_Fwristrotation.jpg', 'Increased mobility and range of motion in wrists.Improves joint and muscle health in wrists.Improved coordination and balance in wrists.\r\nStrengthen and tone surrounding wrist muscles.Enhances overall performance of other body movements and activities.', NULL),
(182, 'Wall Pushups', ' Walk your feet away from the wall and keep your body straight, tightening your core and your buttocks. Now bend your elbows, bringing your chest towards the wall. Now straighten your arms bringing your chest away from the wall.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cc1bc6a49_Fwallpushups.jpg', 'Wall push-ups build strength and endurance, so jobs or chores that require repetitive upper body movements, such as scrubbing, painting, or hammering, can feel easier.', NULL),
(183, 'Arm Circles', 'Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart or sit in a chair with your back straight and your feet on the floor. Move your arms in a forward circle.\r\nMove your arms in a backward circle.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cc4601877_Farmcircle.webp', 'Arm circles can really work on toning the muscles in your shoulder and arm—biceps and triceps. They also work on your upper back muscles. If done along with other workouts that target the arm muscles, arm circles can also help reduce the buildup of fat in your arms.', NULL),
(184, 'Wall Angels', 'Wall angels are performed by placing your butt, back, and head against the wall, then slowly gliding your arms up and down the wall in a “V” to “W” pattern.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cc8988ffe_Fwallangel.jpeg', 'Wall angels are an excellent way to improve spine mobility, posture, and back strength. When incorporated into a healthy fitness routine, they may also help relieve back and neck pain. To get the most out of every wall angel, take it slow and steady and prioritize form. You can do them daily or as often as is comfy.\r\n', NULL),
(185, 'Child Pose', 'The child\'s pose helps to stretch your back and muscles around your hips. In this pose, kneel and sit on your knees. Lean forward, keeping your buttocks on your heels, and rest your forehead on the floor. Move your arms so they\'re next to your legs, palms facing up.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1ccb15daf7_Fchildpose.jpeg', 'Opening your hips.Lengthening your spine.Stretching out your ankles.Relaxing your back muscles.Relieving any tension in your pelvis. Increasing blood flow to your head and neck.', NULL),
(186, 'Warrior Pose', 'Keep your upper body facing the front edge of the mat and your shoulders level. Bend your right knee, the right thigh towards parallel to the floor. Keep the weight in the front heel and big toe. Press the back foot down and lift from the inner arch.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cce76a4cc_Fwarriorpose.jpeg', 'Strengthens your shoulders, arms, legs, ankles and back.Opens yours hips, chest and lungs. Improves focus, balance and stability.Encourages good circulation and respiration.Stretches your arms, legs, shoulders, neck, belly, groins and ankles.', NULL),
(187, 'Armpit Stretch', 'Gently bend your knees while opening up your armpit, then slightly deepen your knee bend until you feel a gentle stretch in your armpit. Straighten and repeat. With each knee bend, stretch a bit further to the point where it feels slightly uncomfortable but not painful.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1cd270337a_Farmpitstreatch.jpg', 'It helps increase flexibility and range of motion. It can help combat slumping over a laptop or keyboard. As you inhale, stretch your arms out to your sides. As you exhale, bring them in front of you, swinging your right arm under your left and grabbing your shoulders with opposite hands.', NULL),
(188, 'Dips', 'Their arms straight down and shoulders over their hands, then lowers their body until their arms are bent to a 90 degree angle at the elbows, and then lifts their body up, returning to the starting position.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d302b7c81_Fdip.jpeg', 'Dip builds strength and muscle mainly in pushing muscle groups. These include chest, triceps and shoulders. They are a great exercise for increasing total upper body strength. The chest dip targets multiple muscle groups at once, making it a compound movement for the chest muscle.', NULL),
(189, 'Reverse Boat Pose', 'Lie down on our stomach. Take a deep breath. Extend our arms forward and raise the arms and legs simultaneously.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d3538b756_Freverseboat.jpeg', 'The posture reduces bulges around the abdomen, hips, and waist. It develops physical and mental strength, coordination, and focus. Back pain: Practicing this yoga posture enhance the health of your back and reduce back pain. Deep relaxation: This posture provides deep relaxation for the shoulder and spine.', NULL),
(190, 'Child Pose', 'The child\'s pose helps to stretch your back and muscles around your hips. In this pose, kneel and sit on your knees. Lean forward, keeping your buttocks on your heels, and rest your forehead on the floor. Move your arms so they\'re next to your legs, palms facing up.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d3953952f_Fchildpose.jpeg', 'Opening your hips.Lengthening your spine.Stretching out your ankles.Relaxing your back muscles.Relieving any tension in your pelvis. Increasing blood flow to your head and neck.\r\n', NULL),
(191, 'Hip Raise', 'Lie faceup on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor.\r\n Squeeze your glutes and press into your heels to raise your hips until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees. Pause, then slowly lower back to the starting position.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d3c67a75b_Fhipraise.webp', ' Hip Thrusts build strength and size in your glutes in a way many other exercises cannot, and experts agree that they provide benefits for many people, from athletes to older adults over age 65. Glute strength is important for the stabilization of your core, pelvis and lower body', NULL);
INSERT INTO `exercises` (`id`, `exerciseName`, `exerciseDescription`, `gender`, `category`, `subCategory`, `level`, `imagePath`, `benefits`, `video_url`) VALUES
(192, 'Y stretch', 'Start by lying face down on the floor. First squeeze your shoulder blades together then raise your arms at a 45-degree angle above your head imagine that your arms form the top of the Y shape and your torso the bottom. Point your thumbs to the ceiling and keep your elbows straight throughout the exercise.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Hand Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d3f729504_Fystretch.jpeg', 'Improve your performance in physical activities. Decrease your risk of injuries.Help your joints move through their full range of motion.Increase muscle blood flow.Enable your muscles to work most effectively.', NULL),
(193, 'Leg Raise', 'Lie face down with your head resting on your hands. Lift your right leg, hold it for a few seconds in the raised position, and then lower it.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d595c7894_Flegraise.jpeg', 'Leg lifts work your core for better stabilization and balance, which leads to better overall control of your body. Leg lifts work the lower abs, \r\nbut they also work the inner thighs (which in Pilates, are considered part of the core). Studies show that having a stable core is essential in preventing injury.', NULL),
(194, 'Warrior Pose', 'Keep your upper body facing the front edge of the mat and your shoulders level. Bend your right knee,the right thigh towards parallel to the floor. Keep the weight in the front heel and big toe. Press the back foot down and lift from the inner arch.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d66bc8c5f_Fwarriorpose.jpeg', 'Strengthens your shoulders, arms, legs, ankles and back.Opens yours hips, chest and lungs.Improves focus, balance and stability.\r\nEncourages good circulation and respiration.Stretches your arms, legs, shoulders, neck, belly, groins and ankles.', NULL),
(195, 'Ball pressing by feetressing by feet', 'Place a medicine ball on the ground and get down into the push-up position with the medicine ball by your feet.\r\n Place your toes on the medicine ball with arms straight. This is the starting position. Step 3: Begin exercise by lowering your chest to the floor\r\n  and pushing yourself back up.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d6c594915_Fballpressing.jpeg', 'Rolling a golf ball under the foot can help relieve discomfort or a feeling of tightness in the arch and ease pain associated with plantar fasciitis. \r\nTo do this exercise: Sit up straight in a chair, with the feet flat on the floor. Place a golf ball — or another small, hard ball — on the floor next to the feet.', NULL),
(196, 'Squats', 'To do a squat, stand with your feet slightly greater than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing ahead. Slowly descend, bending through the hips, \r\nknees and ankles. Stop when your knees reach a 90-degree angle.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d76bc54ae_Fsquat.jpg', ' Squats improve your posture, balance, and mobility.It can help prevent back pain, improve breathing and digestion, and enhance balance. \r\nnd having good balance reduces your risk of falls and other injuries, making your everyday activities easier to perform.', NULL),
(197, 'Knee Stretch', 'Grasp one leg with your hands, holding behind your thigh. Raise your leg in the air with your foot flexed. Straighten the leg as much as \r\npossible without locking the knee. Hold the stretch, return to the starting position, then repeat with the other leg.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d7cf445de_Fkneestretch.jpg', 'Knee stretches reduce tightness in the muscles around your knee. This improves your knee\'s flexibility and mobility, making it easier to move during \r\nexercise and daily activities. Plus, when the muscles around your knee are loose, you\'re less likely to have: knee pain.', NULL),
(199, 'Towel Curls', 'Place your foot on a towel on the floor and scrunch the towel toward you with your toes. Then, also using your toes, push the towel away from you. ', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d8e4d48c1_Ftowelcurl.jpeg', 'The towel curl exercise stretches and flexes the foot to improve balance, support the arches of your feet, and increase overall foot strength.', NULL),
(200, 'Foot Raising', 'Using a counter or chair for support, rise up on your tiptoes, with your knees straight. Slowly lower your feet back down.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e6dc0618a_Ffootraising.jpg', 'Strengthening the Muscles in the Lower Leg:The muscles on the front of the ankle and lower leg may be strengthened, made more mobile, and made more stable by performing toe raises. People may pull the toes and foot up using these muscles, particularly the tibialis anterior, which is a muscle in front of the shin.', NULL),
(201, 'Squats', 'To do a squat, stand with your feet slightly greater than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing ahead. Slowly descend, bending through the hips, knees and ankles. Stop when your knees reach a 90-degree angle.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e70eb0793_Fsquat.jpg', 'Squats improve your posture, balance, and mobility.It can help prevent back pain, improve breathing and digestion, and enhance balance. and having good balance reduces your risk of falls and other injuries, making your everyday activities easier to perform.', NULL),
(202, 'Knee Stretch', 'Grasp one leg with your hands, holding behind your thigh. Raise your leg in the air with your foot flexed. Straighten the leg as much as possible without locking the knee. Hold the stretch, return to the starting position, then repeat with the other leg.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e761d49cf_Fkneestretch.jpg', 'Knee stretches reduce tightness in the muscles around your knee. This improves your knee\'s flexibility and mobility, making it easier to move during exercise and daily activities. Plus, when the muscles around your knee are loose, you\'re less likely to have: knee pain.', NULL),
(203, 'Toes Pushups', 'Start flat on the floor in the proper push-up position. Press into your toes and hover the body, then push all the way up. Lower your knees to the floor as you lower all the way back down again.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e81ad64df_Ftoespushups.webp', 'Push-ups on your toes require not only increased chest and arm strength, but a huge amount of core strength as well: the abdominals, low back and spinal erectors.', NULL),
(204, 'Squats', 'To do a squat, stand with your feet slightly greater than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing ahead. Slowly descend, bending through the hips, knees and ankles. Stop when your knees reach a 90-degree angle.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e847e651e_Fsquat.jpg', 'Squats improve your posture, balance, and mobility.It can help prevent back pain, improve breathing and digestion, and enhance balance. and having good balance reduces your risk of falls and other injuries, making your everyday activities easier to perform.', NULL),
(207, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e8f5e9cad_Fcalfstretch.jpg', 'Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility. Some people perform calf stretches as a warm-up or cool down before or after a lower-body workout routine, yoga practice, cardio session, or standalone \r\nwellness activity.', NULL),
(208, 'Chin Tucks', 'Sit upright and look straight ahead with the ears directly over the shoulders. Place a finger on the chin. Without moving the finger, pull the chin and head straight back until a good stretch is felt at the base of the head and top of the neck.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e94d44f7f_Fchintucks.jpg', 'Reduce headaches. Relieve neck tension.Keep your head aligned above your spine.Allow you to sleep or sit at a desk more comfortably.Improve muscle endurance.\r\n', NULL),
(209, 'Head Side', 'Turning and holding your head on each side is one repetition. With your head facing forward, slowly turn your head to one side as far as is comfortable – you should feel a stretch on the opposite side of your neck.\r\n', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e97adc648_Fheadside.jpg', ' you can gently stretch your neck and help relieve stiffness and pain. Exercises can include: Neck tilts — This involves tilting the neck to one side, holding it for 10 seconds and then repeating the motion on the other side.', NULL),
(210, 'Head Rotation', 'Rotate head gently and slowly from side to side. Do not turn head completely to either side, keep motion small. Keep chin level with ground without letting chin drop to chest.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e9b784ed9_Fheadrotion.jpeg', 'Improves signals from the brain to body. Improves breathing. Improves posture. Improves balance and coordination.Helps prevent injuries. Helps reduce neck and back pain. Helps release tension and stiffness.', NULL),
(211, 'Child Pose', 'The child\'s pose helps to stretch your back and muscles around your hips. In this pose, kneel and sit on your knees. Lean forward, keeping your buttocks on your heels, and rest your forehead on the floor. Move your arms so they\'re next to your legs, palms facing up.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1ea6f3d3a1_Fchildpose.jpeg', 'Opening your hips.Lengthening your spine.Stretching out your ankles.\r\nRelaxing your back muscles.Relieving any tension in your pelvis.Increasing blood flow to your head and neck.', NULL),
(212, 'Meditation', 'Meditation is a mind and body practice focused on interactions between the brain, mind, body, and behavior, containing four key elements: a quiet location with little distractions, a comfortable posture, a focus of attention, and an open attitude.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1eaee5c2c6_Fmeditation.jpg', 'Giving you a new way to look at things that cause stress.Building skills to manage your stress.Making you more self-aware. Focusing on the present.Reducing negative feelings.Helping you be more creative. Helping you be more patient.', NULL),
(213, 'upper Head Stretching ', 'Prepare neck in a neutral position, ears in line with shoulders. \r\nHold the edge of your chair seat with your right hand. Tuck your chin in slightly. Tilt your head to the left, while looking straight ahead.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1ee851c03e_Fupperheadstretching.webp', ' Stretching upper head has been shown to increase serotonin levels — i.e., the hormone that helps stabilize our mood, reduce stress, and overall makes us feel good — which causes a decrease in depression and anxiety.', NULL),
(216, 'Child Pose ', 'The child\'s pose helps to stretch your back and muscles around your hips. In this pose, kneel and sit on your knees. Lean forward, keeping your buttocks on your heels, and rest your forehead on the floor. Move your arms so they\'re next to your legs, palms facing up.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1ef35dee1e_Fchildpose.jpeg', 'Opening your hips.Lengthening your spine.Stretching out your ankles.Relaxing your back muscles.Relieving any tension in your pelvis. Increasing blood flow to your head and neck.', NULL),
(217, 'Meditation', 'Meditation is a mind and body practice focused on interactions between the brain, mind, body, and behavior, containing four key elements: a quiet location with little distractions, a comfortable posture, a focus of attention, and an open attitude.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1ef7194214_Fmeditation.jpg', 'By fundamentally shifting the way we relate to our thoughts and feelings, we can dial down the intensity of emotions that tend to take hold of us, and ultimately experience a greater sense of calm, clarity, and focus in our lives.', NULL),
(218, 'Scapular Retraction', 'It involves pulling the scapulae (or shoulder blades) towards each other, i.e., in the direction of the spine, without the shoulders shrugging upwards. Our normal routine deals with scapular protraction, which is the opposite movement of scapulae away from the spine.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1efb5dd4ff_Fscapular retraction.jpg', 'Performing these exercises can aid in stabilising the shoulder joints, enhancing overall body alignment, and mitigating the risk of upper body injuries. The triangular-shaped scapula bone is situated on each side of the upper back and is crucial in enabling shoulder movement by linking the collarbone to the arm bone.', NULL),
(219, 'Head Rotation', 'Rotate head gently and slowly from side to side. Do not turn head completely to either side, keep motion small. \r\nKeep chin level with ground without letting chin drop to chest.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f01939c48_Fheadrotion.jpeg', 'A few range-of-motion exercises can help target many muscles in your neck. By using the weight of your head alone, you can gently stretch your neck and help relieve stiffness and pain.', NULL),
(220, 'Child pose', 'The child\'s pose helps to stretch your back and muscles around your hips. In this pose, kneel and sit on your knees. Lean forward, keeping your buttocks on your heels, and rest your forehead on the floor. Move your arms so they\'re next to your legs, palms facing up.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f04f56297_Fchildpose.jpeg', 'Opening your hips.Lengthening your spine.Stretching out your ankles.Relaxing your back muscles.Relieving any tension in your pelvis.\r\nIncreasing blood flow to your head and neck.', NULL),
(221, 'Meditation', ' Meditation is a mind and body practice focused on interactions between the brain, mind, body, and behavior, containing four key elements: a quiet location with little distractions, a comfortable posture, a focus of attention, and an open attitude.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f0a96d175_Fmeditation.jpg', 'By fundamentally shifting the way we relate to our thoughts and feelings, we can dial down the intensity of emotions that tend to take hold of us, \r\nand ultimately experience a greater sense of calm, clarity, and focus in our lives.', NULL),
(222, 'Cat-cow Stretch', 'Keep your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees directly below your hips. \r\nInhale deeply while curving your lower back and bringing your head up, tilting your pelvis up like a \"cow.\" \r\nExhale deeply and bring your abdomen in, arching your spine and bringing your head and pelvis down like a \"cat.\"', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f0fe78303_Fcatcowpose.webp', 'The stretch allows the body to relieve stress or pain to the lower back and sciatica. Improves flexibility. Cat cow pose increases the flexibility of the neck, shoulders and spine. The movement also stretches the muscles of the hips, back, abdomen and chest.', NULL),
(223, 'Mountain Climber', 'Performed from a plank position, you\'ll alternate bringing one knee to your chest, then back out again, speeding up each time until you\'re \"running\" against the floor.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f22eaf76e_Fmountainclimb.jpeg', 'Mountain climbers are an effective way of strengthening your arms, back, shoulders, core and legs. Another benefit of using multiple muscles \r\nat once is an increased heart rate, which will help you burn more calories.', NULL),
(224, 'Jumping Jack', 'Begin by standing with your legs straight and your arms to your sides. Jump up and spread your feet beyond hip-width apart while bringing your arms above your head, nearly touching. Jump again, lowering your arms and bringing your legs together.\r\n', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f27436093_Fjumpingjack.jpg', 'Jumping jacks provide full-body exercise.Jumping jacks promote cardiovascular fitness.Jumping jacks boost muscle strength and power.\r\nJumping jacks support strong bones. Jumping jacks enhance balance and coordination.', NULL),
(225, 'Cobra Pose', 'Lie down in a prone position. Lie face down on your mat with your entire body extended.\r\nBring your hands underneath the shoulder blades\r\nBegin to lift your upper body Use lower back muscles to lift higher Look slightly forward and up.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f2b8abcf4_Fcobra.jpg', 'Opens the shoulder blades, neck, and collar bones.Improves spinal posture, flexibility, and alignment.Reduces back pain.Improves circulation.\r\nOpens the lungs.Stimulates the abdominal and digestive organs, improving digestion.', NULL),
(230, 'Mountain Climber', 'Performed from a plank position, you\'ll alternate bringing one knee to your chest, then back out again, speeding up each time until you\'re \"running\" against the floor.\r\n', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f49901b33_Fmountainclimb.jpeg', ' mountain climbers are an effective way of strengthening your arms, back, shoulders, core and legs. Another benefit of using multiple muscles at once is an increased heart rate, which will help you burn more calories.', NULL),
(231, 'Jumping Jack', 'Begin by standing with your legs straight and your arms to your sides. Jump up and spread your feet beyond hip-width apart while bringing your arms above your head, nearly touching. Jump again, lowering your arms and bringing your legs together.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f4c7d95dc_Fjumpingjack.jpg', 'Jumping jacks provide full-body exercise.Jumping jacks promote cardiovascular fitness.Jumping jacks boost muscle strength and power.\r\nJumping jacks support strong bones.Jumping jacks enhance balance and coordination.\r\n', NULL),
(232, 'Squats', ' To do a squat, stand with your feet slightly greater than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing ahead. Slowly descend, bending through the hips, knees and ankles. Stop when your knees reach a 90-degree angle.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f56d823f2_Fsquat.jpg', 'Squatting every day will undoubtedly ramp up the amount of volume that you\'re putting on certain muscle groups. This will in turn allow you to steadily progress in your training while getting through any plateaus you might hit.', NULL),
(234, 'Side Lunges', 'Step one foot out at your side, then sink your hips back and bend your knee to lower your butt to the floor. As you lower to the floor, you\'ll keep your opposite leg straight.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f62896276_Fsidelunges.jpg', 'Side lunges are unique in the way they tone and shape your outer thighs and can get rid of any fat. They can also shape your backside so that it can become strong after many repetitions of side lunge workouts. The sideways movement of side lunges also help you work your quadriceps muscles from another angle.', NULL),
(235, 'Mountain Climber', 'Performed from a plank position, you\'ll alternate bringing one knee to your chest, then back out again, speeding up each time until you\'re \"running\" against the floor.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f6ce7c8d2_Fmountainclimb.jpeg', 'mountain climbers are an effective way of strengthening your arms, back, shoulders, core and legs. Another benefit of using multiple muscles at once is an increased heart rate, which will help you burn more calories.', NULL),
(236, 'Jumping Jack', 'Begin by standing with your legs straight and your arms to your sides. Jump up and spread your feet beyond hip-width apart while bringing your arms above your head, nearly touching. Jump again, lowering your arms and bringing your legs together.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f70c59217_Fjumpingjack.jpg', 'Jumping jacks provide full-body exercise.Jumping jacks promote cardiovascular fitness.Jumping jacks boost muscle strength and power.\r\nJumping jacks support strong bones.Jumping jacks enhance balance and coordination.', NULL),
(237, 'Squats', 'To do a squat, stand with your feet slightly greater than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing ahead. Slowly descend, bending through the hips, knees and ankles. Stop when your knees reach a 90-degree angle.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f7551db03_Fsquat.jpg', 'Squatting every day will undoubtedly ramp up the amount of volume that you\'re putting on certain muscle groups. This will in turn allow you to steadily progress in your training while getting through any plateaus you might hit.', NULL),
(238, 'Crunches', 'An approved crunch begins with you lying down, one knee bent, and hands positioned beneath your lower back for support. \"Do not hollow your stomach or press your back against the floor\", McGill says. Gently lift your head and shoulders, hold briefly and relax back down.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f79fbd269_Fcrunches.jpg', 'Abdominal crunches are an excellent means to burning calories in the body.Abdominal crunches are a highly effective way of improving the balance because \nthey aid in strengthening up the muscles in your abdominal cavity.Abdominal crunches are highly important in improving posture.', NULL),
(239, 'Side plank', 'Lie on your side with your knees bent, and prop your upper body up on your elbow. Raise your hips off the floor, and hold for 6 seconds. Rest for 10 seconds.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1fcace1652_Fsideplank.jpg', 'Side lunges are unique in the way they tone and shape your outer thighs and can get rid of any fat. They can also shape your backside so that it can become strong after many repetitions of side lunge workouts. The sideways movement of side lunges also help you work your quadriceps muscles from another angle.', NULL),
(240, 'Plank', 'Plant hands directly under shoulders (slightly wider than shoulder width) like you\'re about to do a push-up. \r\n Ground toes into the floor and squeeze glutes to stabilize your body. Your legs should be working, too — be careful not to lock or hyperextend your knees.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b2049682b12_Fplank.webp', 'Improves body balance and posture: Apart from muscle growth and endurance, a plank can also help achieve better body balance, posture, as well as coordination. The reason the plank is considered a fundamental part of an exercise routine is because of this.', NULL),
(241, 'Squats', ' To do a squat, stand with your feet slightly greater than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing ahead. Slowly descend, bending through the hips, \r\nknees and ankles. Stop when your knees reach a 90-degree angle.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b20500284ac_Fsquat.jpg', 'Squatting every day will undoubtedly ramp up the amount of volume that you\'re putting on certain muscle groups. This will in turn allow you to steadily progress in your training while getting through any plateaus you might hit.', NULL),
(242, 'Crunches', 'An approved crunch begins with you lying down, one knee bent, and hands positioned beneath your lower back for support. \"Do not hollow your stomach or press your back against the floor\", McGill says. Gently lift your head and shoulders, hold briefly and relax back down.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b20538ac017_Fcrunches.jpg', 'Abdominal crunches are an excellent means to burning calories in the body.Abdominal crunches are a highly effective way of improving the balance because \r\nthey aid in strengthening up the muscles in your abdominal cavity.Abdominal crunches are highly important in improving posture.', NULL),
(243, 'Bridge', 'Lie on your back with your knees bent. Tighten the muscles in your stomach. Raise your hips off the floor until they line up with your knees and shoulders.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b205841accb_Fbridge.jpeg', 'The bridge exercise primarily strengthens your glutes (your butt muscles) and your hamstrings (the muscles in the back of your thigh). \r\nAlong with strengthening, doing bridges increases stability in your core and back muscles. This move can also stretch muscles in your chest, abdomen, and shoulders.', NULL),
(244, 'Pushups', 'From a prone position, the hands are placed under the shoulders with the elbows extended. Keeping the back and legs straight with the toes touching the ground. The body is lowered until the upper arm is parallel to the ground. Then reverse the movement and raise the body until arm is extended.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b205f093f2a_Fpushups.jpeg', 'Improves upper-body strength.Contributes to core stability.Accessible to beginners and seasoned athletes alike.\r\nIs budget friendly.Improves sports performance. Works multiple muscles simultaneously.', NULL),
(245, 'Lying Butterfly', 'Lie back either on the floor or a bolster. Place your hands on your belly or out to the sides. Stay for five to ten breaths, or longer if part of a Yin or Restorative practice. To come out, roll onto your side and use your hands to help you back up to sitting.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b2072246104_Fbutterflypose.jpg', 'It may increase the flexibility of the spine.It may help to tone the lower body.It may relieve physical and mental stress.\r\nIt may improve digestion and relieves constipation.It may relieve tiredness.It may lower the pain in the legs and knees.', NULL),
(246, 'Plank with Hand', ' Push your hands into the ground and raise your torso off the ground. Your body should look as if you\'re in the upward position of a pushup.\r\n Ensure your hands and shoulders are aligned, your legs are straight, your feet are hip-width apart, and your core is engaged.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b20797d8b78_Fplankwithhand.jpg', ' A Healthy Posture.Balance and Coordination.Improves Body Alignment and Helps Avoid Illness. Build Core Strength.Improves Flexibility.\r\nImproves Metabolism.Improves Overall Mental Health.\r\n', NULL),
(247, 'Burpees', 'A position with hands on the floor and legs bent under you, jump back with your legs so they are straight behind you,return to a squat, then stand up again.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b207d747489_Fburpees.jpeg', 'Because burpees target so many muscles and involve a wide range of motion, they can help improve your mobility, balance, and coordination.\r\nWhen you do burpees on a consistent basis, your body will become stronger, your health will improve, and you will move better and feel better.', NULL),
(248, 'Reverse Plank', 'Perform reverse planks by lying on your back with your hands behind your hips. Lift your body up off the floor until your upper body and lower body form a straight line. Engage your core and hold this reverse planking position.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b2081597998_Freverseplank.jpeg', 'Reverse planks activate your core muscles.it work your abdominal muscles, including the rectus abdominis, commonly known as the six-pack muscle. It work your posterior chain. It require no equipment.', NULL),
(249, 'High Praise', 'Do plank with hand carrying some weight in both hands.\r\n', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b208558b045_Fhighpraise.jpg', 'Improves body balance and posture: Apart from muscle growth and endurance, it can also help achieve better body balance, posture, as well as coordination. The reason why high praise is considered a fundamental part of an exercise routine is because of this.', NULL),
(250, 'Right Leg Raise', 'It is performed by lying on the side with support coming from one hand placed on the ground and the opposite foot placed on the ground in front of the lower leg. With the top leg slightly flexed and resting, the bottom leg is abducted upwards against gravity and relaxed down to the ground.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b208a71ed3b_Frightleglift.jpg', 'Besides working the lower abs and inner thighs, leg lifts also help with hip strength and flexibility due to the motion of your legs and hips during the move.\r\n Plus, the move gets your low back involved, which is beneficial for anyone who is interested in strengthening the full core region.', NULL),
(251, 'Left Leg Raise', 'Performed by lying on the side with support coming from one hand placed on the ground and the opposite foot placed on the ground in front of the lower leg. With the top leg slightly flexed and resting, the bottom leg is abducted upwards against gravity and relaxed down to the ground.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b2092179dc9_Flrftlrgraise.jpg', 'Besides working the lower abs and inner thighs, leg lifts also help with hip strength and flexibility due to the motion of your legs and hips during the move.\r\n Plus, the move gets your low back involved, which is beneficial for anyone who is interested in strengthening the full core region.\r\n', NULL),
(252, 'Back Lunges', 'Perform reverse lunges by taking a step backwards, keeping your upper body aligned and your back straight. Lower yourself enough for your front leg to be at a 90-degree angle.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b20a01c8e39_Fbacklunges.jpeg', 'Lunges are one of the best exercises for improving leg strength and balance. Most of the time, they\'re done with a forward motion, but don\'t neglect the power of going backward. A reverse lunge helps develop key hip muscles for better stability and teaches you to control your backward movement and coordination.', NULL),
(253, 'Pushups', 'From a prone position, the hands are placed under the shoulders with the elbows extended. Keeping the back and legs straight with the toes touching the ground. The body is lowered until the upper arm is parallel to the ground. Then reverse the movement and raise the body until arm is extended', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b20aa223a65_Fpushups.jpeg', 'Improves upper-body strength.\r\nContributes to core stability.Accessible to beginners and seasoned athletes alike.Improves sports performance. Works multiple muscles simultaneously.', NULL),
(254, 'Burpees', ' A position with hands on the floor and legs bent under you, jump back with your legs so they are straight behind you,return to a squat, then stand up again.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Gain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b20aeb10607_Fburpees.jpeg', 'Because burpees target so many muscles and involve a wide range of motion, they can help improve your mobility, balance, and coordination. \r\nWhen you do burpees on a consistent basis, your body will become stronger, your health will improve, and you will move better and feel better.', NULL),
(256, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.\r\n', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a017e2ca5_Fprewalking.jpg', 'Walking, especially in the last trimester, helps baby achieve optimal positioning in the uterus. It also helps prevent some of those joint aches and pains by strengthening back muscles. Walking even improves mental health by boosting energy levels as well as mood.\r\n', NULL),
(257, 'Lunges', 'It involves stepping forward, lowering your body toward the ground, and returning back to the starting position. your leg muscles have to control the impact of your foot\'s landing.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b236eacbc1c_Fprelunges.jpeg', 'Lunges stretch the hips and open the pelvis, which helps the baby move into the ideal birthing position. Here\'s how to do them: Stand up straight, then take a big step forward with one leg, keeping your knee over your ankle. The other leg should drop so it\'s parallel to the ground.', NULL),
(258, 'Cat-cow Stretch', 'Keep your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees directly below your hips. Inhale deeply while curving your lower back and bringing your head up, tilting your pelvis up like a \"cow.\" Exhale deeply and bring your abdomen in, arching your spine and bringing your head and pelvis down like a \"cat.\"\r\n', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b2372bb1723_FPrecatstretch.jpeg', 'The pelvic tilting that happens with this pose helps to move the baby into a more comfortable position when experiencing back pain or discomfort from the \r\nbaby’s position during pregnancy.This position is also one of the best for moving a baby into a more favorable position for birthing and can help move a baby from a \r\nposterior position (the one that causes back labor) to an anterior position which is much easier for the baby to move through the pelvis.\r\n', NULL),
(259, 'Triangle Pose', 'The triangle pose is not a forward bend but a sideways movement at the hips performed with straight arms and legs. Avoid bending your back and rounding your spine while performing a triangle pose. Your body should form the shape of the letter “I” rather than “C.”', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b2377597500_Fpretriangle.jpeg', 'The modified triangle pose yoga during pregnancy helps women to restore their balance since their centre of gravity frequently changes and weakens over time. The posture supports the lower back and encourages smooth delivery by stretching and opening the hips.', NULL),
(260, 'Heel Raise', 'Stand with your feet about 10 centimetres apart, with your hands lightly resting on a counter or chair in front of you. Slowly raise your heels off the floor while keeping your knees straight. then slowly lower your heels to the floor.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b39ef15aa8a_Fpreheelraise.jpeg', 'Strengthen calf muscles, improve ankle mobility, and increase stability. They can also be useful for physical therapy, athletic fitness, and general fitness. \r\n', NULL),
(263, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b39fefd0e29_Fprecalfstretch.jpg', 'Exercising during pregnancy comes with many benefits, including promoting muscle strength and endurance to meet the physical demands of pregnancy. It can also help control your blood glucose levels and blood pressure.\r\n', NULL),
(264, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a017e2ca5_Fprewalking.jpg', 'Walking, especially in the last trimester, helps baby achieve optimal positioning in the uterus. It also helps prevent some of those joint aches and pains by strengthening back muscles. Walking even improves mental health by boosting energy levels as well as mood.Walking, especially in the last trimester, helps baby achieve optimal positioning in the uterus. It also helps prevent some of those joint aches and pains by strengthening back muscles. Walking even improves mental health by boosting energy levels as well as mood.', NULL),
(266, 'Warrior Pose', 'Keep your upper body facing the front edge of the mat and your shoulders level. Bend your right knee, the right thigh towards parallel to the floor. Keep the weight in the front heel and big toe. Press the back foot down and lift from the inner arch.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a07d01ebb_Fprewarriorpose2.jpg', 'The prenatal warrior pose is considered safe during the second and third trimesters of pregnancy. This pose is known to strengthen your legs and also help boost your mental health. It tones the arms, legs, and lower back. Improves balance and stability.', NULL),
(267, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.\r\n', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a0a51e62d_Fprewalking.jpg', 'Walking, especially in the last trimester, helps baby achieve optimal positioning in the uterus. It also helps prevent some of those joint aches and pains by strengthening back muscles. Walking even improves mental health by boosting energy levels as well as mood.', NULL),
(268, 'Leg Lift', 'A leg lift, also called a leg lowering exercise, is a core exercise you do lying on your back. It involves lifting and lowering your legs in a controlled manner. ', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a0ce408d0_Fpreleglift.jpg', 'Leg lifts are a good way to strengthen your back and abdominal muscles. However, during pregnancy, leg lifts should be modified after 20 weeks to avoid lying on your back.', NULL),
(269, 'GluteBbridge', 'Glute bridges are done by laying on your back with both feet planted on the ground and lifting your pelvis. It can help to increase hip flexibility and lower back health.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a0f997cbf_Fpreglutebridge.jpeg', 'Bridges are an excellent exercise during pregnancy because stronger glutes help to alleviate low back and pelvic pain. As mentioned above, standard bridges do not require a modification because you are on your back and moving.', NULL),
(270, 'Malasana', 'As you find your hips lowering down toward the earth, keep your spine long. Allow your elbows to gently press on to the inner thighs or knees,As you do so, lift your chest up toward your thumbs. Now breathe.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a127e5601_Fpremalasana.jpg', 'If there\'s one yoga pose that\'s almost practiced in every prenatal yoga program, it\'s Malasana Squats during pregnancy provide quite amazing stretch to the groin area, opening the hips, and beginning to make space down there for a baby to form his grand exit.', NULL),
(271, 'Wide Squats', 'With your feet placed outside of hip width (wide), hold a pair of dumbbells in your hands. Slowly descend by bending your hips and knees. Keep your back straight and your chest up, and maintain the weight on your heels.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a162c9cd0_Fprewidesquats.jpg', 'Squats do wonders to prepare the body for labor, and they\'re a great prenatal exercise to target the pelvic floor muscles. The pelvic floor stretches and lengthens as you bend down into a squat, and you engage and lift your pelvic floor as you return back to standing.', NULL),
(272, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Postnatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a195919a7_Fwalking.jpg', 'Walking, especially in the last trimester, helps baby achieve optimal positioning in the uterus. It also helps prevent some of those joint aches and pains by strengthening back muscles. Walking even improves mental health by boosting energy levels as well as mood.', NULL),
(274, 'Wall Slide', 'It involves pressing your forearms against a wall and sliding your arms up and down.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Postnatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a2472ab78_Fwallslide.jpeg', 'This exercise helps to add strength to your lower body, including your thighs, butt, and hips. Prop a yoga ball against a wall and stand straight with your bottom and lower back resting on the ball. With your feet flat on the floor and about hip width apart, slowly bend your knees and slide down the wall.\r\n', NULL),
(275, 'Plank', 'Lie facedown with your forearms on the floor, with your legs extended and your feet together. You can use a mat or towel to make this more comfortable. Push into your forearms as you raise your body so it forms a straight line from your head and neck to your feet.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Postnatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3ae4b3783a_Fpostplank.jpeg', 'Upport for your pelvic floor muscles, preventing issues like frequent urination during pregnancy and postpartum. Increased lower back support, improving back pain caused by the pull of your baby bump. An easier labor and postpartum recovery.', NULL),
(276, 'Side Lunges', 'Keeping right knee bent at a 90-degree angle, lift right leg out to the side. Stop when the right knee is at, or just below, parallel to the floor.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Postnatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3ae70baf95_Fsidelunges.jpg', 'During the later stages of pregnancy, your lower body bears all the extra weight. Practising stepping lunges during pregnancy is highly beneficial to strengthen the lower body. Additionally, it might help in maintaining the balance of the body as the centre of gravity shifts during pregnancy.\r\n', NULL),
(277, 'Donkey Kick', 'Keeping right knee bent at a 90-degree angle, lift right leg out to the side. Stop when the right knee is at, or just below, parallel to the floor.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Postnatal', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3ae9f67987_Fdonkeykicks.jpg', 'The donkey kick helps stabilize your core. You have to balance in this position, which strengthens core muscles and gives you better balance in other exercises and daily movements.', NULL),
(280, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Postnatal', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3af504e5c2_Fwalking.jpg', 'Walking, especially in the last trimester, helps baby achieve optimal positioning in the uterus. It also helps prevent some of those joint aches and pains by strengthening back muscles. Walking even improves mental health by boosting energy levels as well as mood. ', NULL),
(281, 'Jumping Jack', 'Begin by standing with your legs straight and your arms to your sides. Jump up and spread your feet beyond hip-width apart while bringing your arms above your head, nearly touching. Jump again, lowering your arms and bringing your legs together.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Postnatal', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3af710fe91_Fjumpingjack.jpg', 'Moderate jumping during pregnancy is unlikely to pose harm. However, if you are new to such activities or in the first trimester, it is advisable to avoid jumping exercises and focus on other safe pregnancy workouts.\r\n', NULL),
(282, 'Side Lunges', 'Keeping right knee bent at a 90-degree angle, lift right leg out to the side. Stop when the right knee is at, or just below, parallel to the floor.', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Postnatal', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3af96f053c_Fsidelunges.jpg', 'During the later stages of pregnancy, your lower body bears all the extra weight. Practising stepping lunges during pregnancy is highly beneficial to strengthen the lower body. Additionally, it might help in maintaining the balance of the body as the centre of gravity shifts during pregnancy.', NULL),
