(320, 'Wrist Motion', 'Get into position on your hands and knees, with the fingers pointing toward the body. Slowly lean forward, keeping your elbows straight. Hold the position Relax, then repeat the stretch.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b69e018b6_Fwristmotion.jpg', 'Increase motion of the wrist joint.Improve the function of the wrist joint as well as the whole limb. Improve motion efficiency.Increase independence.Decrease wrist pain.Increase as well as maintain wrist joint integrity.', NULL),
(322, 'Hand Stretches', 'Hold one hand at chest level with the elbow bent. With the other hand, grasp the thumb side of the hand and bend your wrist downward. To increase the stretch, bend your wrist toward your little finger. Repeat the same exercise with a straight arm. Switch hands and repeat.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b6f94d1f7_Fhandstretches.jpg', 'Strengthen the muscles around the joints for better support. Increase the circulation of synovial fluid (lubricates and helps cushion the joints to keep them moving smoothly). Improve blood flow to your hands, warming the muscles and ligaments.', NULL),
(323, 'Grip Stretch', 'Fingers back, palms on the desk: Stretch by leaning back and forth on your bodyweight and gently side to side.Fingers back, palms off the desk: Lifting your palms up places the emphasis on your fingers more.Clenched fists: While seated, place your hands on your things with palms up.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b712af3c0_Fgripstrenth.jpeg', 'Reduced hand aging process. Increased muscle and skeletal mass .Increased independence to engage in everyday tasks. Improved cognitive, physical and overall holistic health.', NULL),
(324, 'Tendon Glides', 'Bend both the knuckle and middle finger joints so that your fingers are resting on the base of your palm. Keep your fingers straight. From the open-palm position, slowly engage all your fingers, thumb, and joints to create a fist and squeeze gently.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b740bf8ac_Ftendonglides.png', 'Tendon glide exercises can help prevent repetitive trauma to the hands, writs and elbows. There may be some discomfort when starting the exercises,but that should decrease in a day or two. If it does not improve or go away, seek advice from your health care professional.', NULL),
(325, 'Finger Stretch', 'Finger extensor stretch Lay your hand out flat on a table or solid surface.Use your other hand to hold the affected finger.Slowly lift up the finger and keep the rest of your fingers flat.Lift and stretch the finger as high as it will go without straining. Hold it here for a few seconds and release it back down.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b75e1b8b1_Ffingerstretch.jpeg', 'The practice of this exercise promotes blood circulation, help release stiffness, and reduces the frequency of cramps, when done as part of both warm-up and cool down.\r\n', NULL),
(327, 'Finger Raising', 'Put your finger on some surface and gently raise one finger one by one at a time.\r\n', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b799a895c_Ffingerraising.jpg', 'Use this exercise to help increase the range of motion and flexibility in your fingers. Place your hand flat, palm down, on a table or other surface. Gently lift one finger at a time off of the table and then lower it. You can also lift all your fingers and thumb at once, and then lower.', NULL),
(328, 'Thumb Touching', 'Start touching your thumb with remaining fingers of hand one by one at a time.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b7b449b09_Fthumbtouching.jpeg', 'This exercise will increase blood circulation in hands and fingers so that it will improve condition of balance and hurting.\r\n', NULL),
(329, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b7cebb17c_Fcalfstretch.jpg', 'Tight calf muscles or injuries can lead to foot and leg pain, including plantar fasciitis, shin splints, Achilles tendonitis, and knee pain. Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility.', NULL),
(330, 'Triceps Stretch', 'Bring your left elbow straight up while bending your arm. Grab your left elbow with your right hand, and pull your left elbow toward  your head with light pressure. If you are more flexible, you may pull your arm slightly behind your head. You will feel the stretch along the back of your arm.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b7ea63979_Ftricepsstretch.jpg', 'Triceps stretches improve flexibility, lengthen muscles, and increase range of motion. Plus, they can help to prevent tight muscles,loosen connective tissue, and boost circulation, all while using no or minimal equipment.\r\n', NULL),
(331, 'Hand Stretches', ' Hold one hand at chest level with the elbow bent. With the other hand, grasp the thumb side of the hand and bend your wrist downward. To increase the stretch, bend your wrist toward your little finger. Repeat the same exercise with a straight arm. Switch hands and repeat.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b80b1dfb4_Fhandstretches.jpg', 'Hand and wrist exercises can improve mobility and decrease the chance of injury or reinjury. Various hand and wrist stretches can help with strengthening.Wrist stretches are easy to do at home or at the office. When done properly, they can benefit a person\'s overall wrist and hand health.', NULL),
(332, 'Tendon Glides', 'Bend both the knuckle and middle finger joints so that your fingers are resting on the base of your palm. Keep your fingers straight.From the open-palm position, slowly engage all your fingers, thumb, and joints to create a fist and squeeze gently.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b83011a24_Ftendonglides.png', 'Tendon glide exercises can help prevent repetitive trauma to the hands, writs and elbows. There may be some discomfort when starting the exercises, but that should decrease in a day or two. If it does not improve or go away, seek advice from your health care professional.', NULL),
(333, 'Hand Squeezes', 'Hold a soft ball in your palm and squeeze it as hard as you can. Hold for a few seconds and release.Repeat 10 to 15 times on each hand. Do this exercise two to three times a week, but rest your hands for 48 hours in between sessions.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b854907fa_Fhandsqueezes.jpeg', 'Builds endurance.Increases the power to lift heavy objects.Quality of life.Sports performance is upper .Growth of forearms.Boosts mental health.', NULL),
(334, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.\r\n', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b8706ba44_Fcalfstretch.jpg', 'Tight calf muscles or injuries can lead to foot and leg pain, including plantar fasciitis, shin splints, Achilles tendonitis, and knee pain. Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility.', NULL),
(335, 'Writting', 'Writting is the best therapy for contraction of muscles of hands.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b88906670_Fwriting.jpg', 'The rate of your body will increases which helps to burn calories. Moreover, it also helps in improving the oxygen level and blood flow of the body. When you exercise daily, your brain cells will release frequently. This helps in producing cells in the hippocampus.', NULL),
(336, 'Head Movement', 'Bending Your head left to right side of your body towards your shoulders is head movment.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b8ac6aa5d_Fheadmovement.jpeg', 'Moving the head involves flexion and contraction of the neck muscles. The resulting head positions are up and down (nodding), left and right (shaking the head),and tilted (ear to shoulder).', NULL),
(337, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b8c7d8e25_Fwalking.jpg', 'like outdoor walking, walking indoors — either up and down the hallway or in-place — can be beneficial for weight loss if you reach high intensities. A key to maximizing the benefits of at-home walking workouts is by minimizing the sedentary (TV viewing) times and making the most of incidental activities.', NULL),
(338, 'Sit Stand', 'Sit in a chair with your feet apart while holding your hands together in front of your chest. Without using your hands, push through your feet to stand and hold this position.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b8eab6682_Fsitstand.jpg', 'Improved ability to do everyday activities, such as sitting down, standing up, or climbing stairs without pain.Better balance .Increased mobility, especially in the knees, hips, and ankles. Improved muscular endurance.', NULL),
(339, 'Ball Catching', 'Ball catching is one of the great exercise for vertigo because it can increase mental stability and min consiousness.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b9143bb93_Fballcatching.jpeg', 'In various clinical settings, exercises using ball throwing and catching activities have been broadly used to improve balance, gait, or proprioceptive functions and to reduce the risk of athletic injuries.', NULL),
(340, 'Touch Toes', 'Lay on your back, with your legs extending up vertically towards the ceiling. Extend your arms forward, keeping them straight. They should be parallel to your legs. Crunch forwards, reaching up to your toes with your outstretched arms.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b93604d7d_Ftouchtoes.jpg', 'The overall benefit of being able to touch your toes is having proper flexibility in your hamstrings, calves, and lower back. Being able to touch your toes reflects good flexibility in these areas.\r\n', NULL),
(341, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b95348603_Fwalking.jpg', 'Much like outdoor walking, walking indoors — either up and down the hallway or in-place — can be beneficial for weight loss if you reach high intensities. A key to maximizing the benefits of at-home walking workouts is by minimizing the sedentary (TV viewing) times and making the most of incidental activities.', NULL),
(342, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg.Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b7cebb17c_Fcalfstretch.jpg', 'Tight calf muscles or injuries can lead to foot and leg pain, including plantar fasciitis, shin splints, Achilles tendonitis, and knee pain. Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility.', NULL),
(343, 'Hip Raise', 'Lie on an exercise mat with your knees bent so that your feet are flat on the floor. Keep your back straight. Place your hands out to your sides palms flat for stability. Raise your glutes off the floor by extending your hips upward while pushing down through you heels.\r\n', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b9929f603_Fhipraise.webp', 'Hip raise build strength and size in your glutes in a way many other exercises cannot, and experts agree that they provide benefits for many people, from athletes to older adults over.Glute strength is important for the stabilization of your core, pelvis and lower body.', NULL),
(344, 'Head Side', 'Rotate head gently and slowly from side to side. Do not turn head completely to either side, keep motion small. Keep chin level with ground without letting chin drop to chest. ', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e97adc648_Fheadside.jpg', 'Improves signals from the brain to body.Improves breathing.Improves posture.Improves balance and coordination.Helps prevent injuries.Helps reduce neck and back pain.Helps release tension and stiffness.\r\n', NULL),
(345, 'Child Pose', 'In this pose, kneel and sit on your knees. Lean forward, keeping your buttocks on your heels, and rest your forehead on the floor. Move your arms so they\'re next to your legs, palms facing up.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b9d088441_Fchildpose.jpeg', 'Opening your hips.Lengthening your spine.Stretching out your ankles.Relaxing your back muscles.Relieving any tension in your pelvis. Increasing blood flow to your head and neck.', NULL),
(346, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b9f400a84_Fwalking.jpg', 'Much like outdoor walking, walking indoors — either up and down the hallway or in-place — can be beneficial for weight loss if you reach high intensities. A key to maximizing the benefits of at-home walking workouts is by minimizing the sedentary (TV viewing) times and making the most of incidental activities.\r\n', NULL),
(347, 'Meditation', 'Meditation is a mind and body practice focused on interactions between the brain, mind, body, and behavior, containing four key elements:a quiet location with little distractions, a comfortable posture, a focus of attention, and an open attitude.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3ba0e9a15b_Fmeditation.jpg', 'Meditating before a workout will help you relax and de-stress before you get started. It can also help you focus and better control your movements throughout. However, meditating after a workout can reduce your stress hormone levels, reduce pain, and improve your recovery.', NULL),
(349, 'Touch Toes', 'Lay on your back, with your legs extending up vertically towards the ceiling. Extend your arms forward, keeping them straight. They should be parallel to your legs. Crunch forwards, reaching up to your toes with your outstretched arms.\r\n', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3ba489532c_Ftouchtoes.jpg', 'The overall benefit of being able to touch your toes is having proper flexibility in your hamstrings, calves, and lower back. Being able to touch your toes reflects good flexibility in these areas.', NULL),
(350, 'Calf Stretch', 'Stand facing a wall with your hands on the wall at about eye level. Put the leg you want to stretch about a step behind your other leg. Keeping your back heel on the floor, bend your front knee until you feel a stretch in the back leg.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3ba6252c1e_Fcalfstretch.jpg', 'Tight calf muscles or injuries can lead to foot and leg pain, including plantar fasciitis, shin splints, Achilles tendonitis, and knee pain.\r\n Stretching your calves activates the muscles, stimulates blood flow, and can increase your short-term range of motion and flexibility.', NULL),
(351, 'Cat-cow stretch', ' Keep your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees directly below your hips. Inhale deeply while curving your lower back and bringing your head up, tilting your pelvis up like a \"cow.\"  Exhale deeply and bring your abdomen in, arching your spine and bringing your head and pelvis down like a \"cat.\"', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b51087bbacb_Fcatcowpose.webp', 'Stretches muscles,Stimulates abdominal organs, Improves flexibility, Improves posture,Aligns the spine, Back pain relief.', NULL),
(352, 'Foot raising', 'Using a counter or chair for support, rise up on your tiptoes, with your knees straight. Slowly lower your feet back down.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b517df7f399_Ffootraising.jpg', 'Strengthening the Muscles in the Lower Leg:The muscles on the front of the ankle and lower leg may be strengthened, made more mobile, and made more stable by performing toe raises. People may pull the toes and foot up using these muscles, particularly the tibialis anterior, which is a muscle in front of the shin.', NULL),
(354, 'Meditation', 'Meditation is a mind and body practice focused on interactions between the brain, mind, body, and behavior, containing four key elements: a quiet location with little distractions, a comfortable posture, a focus of attention, and an open attitude.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b51a4f6aacc_Fmeditation.jpg', 'By fundamentally shifting the way we relate to our thoughts and feelings, we can dial down the intensity of emotions that tend to take hold of us, and ultimately experience a greater sense of calm, clarity, and focus in our lives.', NULL),
(355, 'Head Rotation', 'Rotate head gently and slowly from side to side. Do not turn head completely to either side, keep motion small. Keep chin level with ground without letting chin drop to chest', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b51cf29d04f_Fheadrotion.jpeg', 'A few range-of-motion exercises can help target many muscles in your neck. By using the weight of your head alone, you can gently \r\nstretch your neck and help relieve stiffness and pain.', NULL),
(356, 'Crunches', 'An approved crunch begins with you lying down, one knee bent, and hands positioned beneath your lower back for support. \"Do not hollow your stomach or press your back against the floor\", McGill says. Gently lift your head and shoulders, hold briefly and relax back down.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b52fa7cd351_Fcrunches.jpg', 'Abdominal crunches are an excellent means to burning calories in the body .Abdominal crunches are a highly effective way of improving the balance because they aid in strengthening up the muscles in your abdominal cavity. Abdominal crunches are highly important in improving posture.', NULL),
(357, 'Cobra Pose', 'Lie down in a prone position. Lie face down on your mat with your entire body extended. Bring your hands underneath the shoulder blades. Begin to lift your upper body. Use lower back muscles to lift higher. Look slightly forward and up. Lower down gently. Transition to the next posture.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Asthma', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b7a4774a640_Fcobra.jpg', 'Sitting cross-legged with a straight spine and hands resting on the knees can help improve lung function and reduce asthma symptoms. Cobra Pose: This backbend pose can help expand the chest and improve lung capacity.', NULL),
(359, 'Thoraic stretch', 'Sitting tall in a chair with your back resting against the back rest. Take both arms forwards to shoulder height with the hands together. Pause to take a breath in then exhale as you let the arms reach above your head and stretch back over the chair. Pause and return to starting position.', 'Male', 'Body Pain', 'Back Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65a0cae1defab_Mthoraicstretch.png', ' Healthier shoulders.Reduced neck and low back pain.Increased lung volume.', NULL),
(361, 'Jumping Jack', 'Begin by standing with your legs straight and your arms to your sides. Jump up and spread your feet beyond hip-width apart while bringing \r\nyour arms above your head, nearly touching. Jump again, lowering your arms and bringing your legs together.', 'Male', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b9af4f2d683_Mjumpingjack.jpeg', 'Moderate jumping during pregnancy is unlikely to pose harm. However, if you are new to such activities or in the first trimester, it is advisable to avoid jumping exercises and focus on other safe pregnancy workouts.', NULL),
(362, 'Jumping Jack', 'Begin by standing with your legs straight and your arms to your sides. Jump up and spread your feet beyond hip-width apart while \r\nbringing your arms above your head, nearly touching. Jump again, lowering your arms and bringing your legs together.', 'Male', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b9b142bed60_Mjumpingjack.jpeg', 'Moderate jumping during pregnancy is unlikely to pose harm. However, if you are new to such activities or in the first trimester, it is advisable to avoid jumping exercises and focus on other safe pregnancy workouts.', NULL),
(363, 'Jumping Jack', 'Begin by standing with your legs straight and your arms to your sides. Jump up and spread your feet beyond hip-width apart while bringing \r\nyour arms above your head, nearly touching. Jump again, lowering your arms and bringing your legs together.', 'Male', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65a0fc0ac895a_Mjumpingjack.jpeg', 'Jumping jacks provide full-body exercise.Jumping jacks promote cardiovascular fitness.Jumping jacks boost muscle strength and power.\r\nJumping jacks support strong bones.Jumping jacks enhance balance and coordination.', NULL),
(364, 'Child pose', ' The child\'s pose helps to stretch your back and muscles around your hips. In this pose, kneel and sit on your knees. Lean forward, keeping your buttocks on your heels, and rest your forehead on the floor. Move your arms so they\'re next to your legs, palms facing up.', 'Male', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b9b3168808d_Mchildpose.jpeg', 'Opening your hips. Lengthening your spine. Stretching out your ankles. Relaxing your back muscles. Relieving any tension in your pelvis.\nIncreasing blood flow to your head and neck.', NULL),
(365, 'Wrist Motion', 'Get into position on your hands and knees, with the fingers pointing toward the body.\r\nSlowly lean forward, keeping your elbows straight.\r\nHold the position Relax, then repeat the stretch.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65af65fe0797f_Mwristmotion.jpg', 'Increase motion of the wrist joint.Improve the function of the wrist joint as well as the whole limb.\r\nImprove motion efficiency.Increase independence.Decrease wrist pain.Increase as well as maintain wrist joint integrity.', NULL),
(366, 'Trunk Rotation', 'Exhale and slowly rotate your torso in one direction, keeping your upper arms at your sides, elbows bent and hands positioned at the midline of your body. Your head, chest and torso should all move together and avoid leaning your torso in the direction of your movement.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Stroke', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b9b6ac1dcc9_Mtrunkrotation.jpeg', 'Increase trunk rotation, flexibility, and range of motion Decrease the risk of injury. Improve functional fitness Relieve back tension. Reduce low back pain.', NULL),
(367, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least \r\nthree times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Stroke', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b9b62e8e512_Mwalking.jpeg', 'Daily walking helps to improve your lungs capacity, in other words, the maximum amount of oxygen your body can use. Also, exercise increases\r\n blood flow to your lungs, promoting blood flow to the heart which pumps oxygen throughout your body.', NULL),
(368, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Stroke', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b9b62e8e512_Mwalking.jpeg', 'Muscle and strength. Cardiovascular health. Balance. Resilience. Stamina. Overall physical fitness. Mobile capability.', NULL),
(369, 'Head Movement', 'Bending Your head left to right side of your body towards your shoulders is head movement.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b9baa5ec59a_Mheadmovement.jpeg', 'Moving the head involves flexion and contraction of the neck muscles. The resulting head positions are up and down (nodding), left and right (shaking the head),and tilted (ear to shoulder).', NULL),
(370, 'Ball Catching ', 'Ball catching is one of the great exercise for vertigo because it can increase mental stability and minimum consiousness.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b9bb1860ddb_Mballcatching.jpg', ' In various clinical settings, exercises using ball throwing and catching activities have been broadly used to improve balance, gait, or proprioceptive functions and to reduce the risk of athletic injuries.', NULL),
(371, 'Walking', 'Don\'t walk immediately after a big meal. Build activity slowly – start with a 20 minute walk then increase gradually. Try to walk at least three times per week. Use the correct technique – walk at a steady pace, swing your arms freely and stand as straight as you can.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b9b62e8e512_Mwalking.jpeg', 'Much like outdoor walking, walking indoors — either up and down the hallway or in-place — can be beneficial for weight loss if you reach high intensities. A key to maximizing the benefits of at-home walking workouts is by minimizing the sedentary (TV viewing) times and making the most of incidental activities.', NULL),
(372, 'Child pose', ' The child\'s pose helps to stretch your back and muscles around your hips. In this pose, kneel and sit on your knees. Lean forward, keeping your buttocks on your heels, and rest your forehead on the floor. Move your arms so they\'re next to your legs, palms facing up.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b9bc8aa605f_Mchildpose.jpeg', 'Opening your hips. Lengthening your spine. Stretching out your ankles. Relaxing your back muscles. Relieving any tension in your pelvis.\r\nIncreasing blood flow to your head and neck.', NULL),
(373, 'Sun Salutations', 'Sun Salutations, also called Surya Namaskars or \"Sun Salutes\" by yogi practitioners, are a 12-posture sequence of flowing movements \r\nthat offer an entire body stretch, counterbalancing bending of the spine, and an opening of the heart, shoulders, and chest.', 'Male', 'Disease', 'Asthma', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65a11311e2f69_Msunsalutation.jpg', 'Sun salutation enhances the overall health especially the health of inner organs. Thus, it significantly improves the immunity system. \r\nThe emphasis is given on the breath while performing each sequence. It opens up the chest, enhances lung capacity, and strengthens the respiratory system.', NULL),
(374, 'Hand Squeezes', 'Hold a soft ball in your palm and squeeze it as hard as you can.Hold for a few seconds and release.Repeat 10 to 15 times on each hand. Do this exercise two to three times a week, but rest your hands for 48 hours in between sessions.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b77c97823_Fhandsqueezes.jpeg', 'Builds endurance.Increases the power to lift heavy objects.Quality of life. Sports performance is upper .Growth of forearms. Boosts mental health.', NULL),
(375, 'Seated Marching', 'This is a hip flexor activation exercise. Start by sitting down on any comfortable surface and maintain a neutral spine. Raise one knee up as high as possible without breaking neutral spine position and lower it back down. Repeat for the opposite hip.', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Stroke', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b3b42250e47_Fseatedmarching.jpg', 'It improves balance: The act of marching can help to improve your body\'s stability, which is particularly beneficial for aging seniors. The very motion fosters a fundamental component of body movement known as dynamic balance control – or the ability to maintain stability while in motion.', NULL),
(376, 'Cat-cow Stretch', 'Keep your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees directly below your hips. Inhale deeply while curving your lower back and bringing your head up, tilting your pelvis up like a \"cow.\" Exhale deeply and bring your abdomen in, arching your spine and bringing your head and pelvis down like a \"cat.\"\r\n', 'Female', 'Disease', 'Vertigo', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b3ba29425c7_Fcatcowpose.webp', 'The stretch allows the body to relieve stress or pain to the lower back and sciatica. Improves flexibility. Cat cow pose increases the flexibility of the neck, shoulders and spine. The movement also stretches the muscles of the hips, back, abdomen and chest.', NULL),
(377, 'Tree Pose', 'Tucking one leg into the other while your hands are in a prayer position above your head, resembling a tree. This pose can improve balance, stability, and strengthen your core.\r\n', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65bb3325659e2_Fpretreepose2.jpg', 'Improves Balance, Strength, and Stability in the Legs.Improves Concentration and Awareness. Enhances Neuromuscular Coordination.\r\nOpens the Hips and Strengthens Its Bones.', NULL),
(378, 'Wide Squats', 'With your feet placed outside of hip width (wide), hold a pair of dumbbells in your hands. Slowly descend by bending your hips and knees. Keep your back straight and your chest up, and maintain the weight on your heels.\r\n', 'Female', 'Pregnancy', 'Prenatal', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b3a162c9cd0_Fprewidesquats.jpg', 'Squats do wonders to prepare the body for labor, and they\'re a great prenatal exercise to target the pelvic floor muscles. The pelvic floor stretches and lengthens as you bend down into a squat, and you engage and lift your pelvic floor as you return back to standing.', NULL),
(379, 'Plyo Side Lunges', 'Lower your body into a lateral lunge on the left, keeping chest high. Simultaneously reach right hand down to the floor in front of you. Push through left foot to hop back up to wide-stance position.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Advanced', 'uploads/images/image_65b1e8802396e_Fplyolunge.jpeg', 'Plyo lunges are a full-body workout. When performed properly, It build muscle in both your lower body and core, making them a great addition to your high-intensity interval training (HIIT workout).They are an aerobic exercise.They are a convenient home workout.', NULL);
INSERT INTO `exercises` (`id`, `exerciseName`, `exerciseDescription`, `gender`, `category`, `subCategory`, `level`, `imagePath`, `benefits`, `video_url`) VALUES
(381, 'Cat-cow Stretch', 'Keep your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees directly below your hips. Inhale deeply while curving your lower back and bringing your head up, tilting your pelvis up like a \"cow.\" Exhale deeply and bring your abdomen in, arching your spine and bringing your head and pelvis down like a \"cat.\"', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Head Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1eec0126f3_Fcatcowpose.webp', 'The stretch allows the body to relieve stress or pain to the lower back and sciatica. Improves flexibility. Cat cow pose increases the flexibility of the neck, shoulders and spine. The movement also stretches the muscles of the hips, back, abdomen and chest.', NULL),
(382, 'Donkey Kicks', 'Sitting tall in a chair with your back resting against the back rest. \r\nTake both arms forwards to shoulder height with the hands together. \r\nPause to take a breath in then exhale as you let the arms reach above your head and stretch back over the chair.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f351a02d1_Fdonkeykicks.jpg', 'Donkey kicks target the gluteus maximus and medius. Without equipment, you can use this exercise to tighten and tone the glutes and core, preparing you for more advanced variations (think pulses) and improving your overall fitness level.', NULL),
(383, 'Wall Pushups', ' Walk your feet away from the wall and keep your body straight, tightening your core and your buttocks.\r\n Now bend your elbows, bringing your chest towards the wall. Now straighten your arms bringing your chest away from the wall.', 'Female', 'Weight', 'Weight Loss', 'Beginner', 'uploads/images/image_65b1f3139add5_Fwallpushup.jpg', 'Wall push-ups build strength and endurance, so jobs or chores that require repetitive upper body movements, such as scrubbing, painting, or hammering, can feel easier.', NULL),
(198380, 'Elbow to Knee Touch', 'Standing with hips shoulder width apart, rotate your torso and bend an elbow on one side of the body and flex the hip of the \r\nother side of the body to bring one elbow to an opposite knee.', 'Female', 'Body Pain', 'Leg Pain', 'Intermediate', 'uploads/images/image_65b1d8a5758a7_Felbowtoknee.webp', 'This elbows to knees exercise can help improve cardiovascular health, decrease back and joint stiffness, and strengthen core muscles that\r\n help the spine balance weight.', NULL);
